<subSubSection pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="82.[189,457,981,1007]" box="[189,457,981,1007]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,457,981,1007]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,457,981,1007]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="82.[189,1399,1028,1231]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[189,563,1028,1054]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ghatsi" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[189,563,1028,1054]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) ghatsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[570,661,1028,1054]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is not particularly similar to any other known 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[1207,1316,1028,1054]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1207,1316,1028,1054]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Sphegina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the key it runs to couplet 31 together with 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[630,1012,1063,1089]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prolixa" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[630,1012,1063,1089]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) prolixa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1017,1106,1063,1089]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Except for the characters mentioned in the key, the species can be separated by their strikingly different genitalia, particularly the superior lobes. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[399,551,1134,1161]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ghatsi" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[399,551,1134,1161]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">S. (A.) ghatsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[558,648,1134,1160]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the superior lobe is very simple and short subtriangular whereas in 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[221,389,1170,1197]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prolixa" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[221,389,1170,1197]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">S. (A.) prolixa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[398,490,1170,1196]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
it is long, curved and posteriorly bilobed, with the ventral lobe exceedingly long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
