<paragraph blockId="84.[189,1399,367,500]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
LEGS. Pro- and mesoleg yellow, tarsomeres 4 and 5 black. Metaleg, 
<figureCitation box="[970,1072,367,393]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="78.[189,232,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,785,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@78.[189,1399,785,1777]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="Fig. 33. Metaleg, anterior view. A. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) crassispina Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, paratype, ♀, Myanmar. B. S. (A.) crucivena Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, paratype, Ƌ, Myanmar. C. S. (A.) exilipes sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Java. D. S. (A.) forficata Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, paratype, Ƌ, Myanmar. E. S. (A.) ghatsi sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, India. F. S. (A.) gigantea sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. G. S. (A.) gigas Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, paratype, ♀, Myanmar. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830617" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830617/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Fig. 33E</figureCitation>
, with coxa black, trochanter yellow; femur black with basal 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[561,583,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">⅓</emphasis>
yellow, strongly incrassate, ratio width: length 1: 3.0; tibia black and yellow biannulate with long and wide apicoventral dens; tarsus entirely black, basitarsomere thick, ratio width: length 1: 3.2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="84.[189,1399,540,745]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
ABDOMEN. Length ratio of terga I: II: III: IV 1: 3.2: 2.0: 1.8; ratio width at posterior margin: medial length of tergum II and III 1: 2.7 and 1: 0.7. Terga black, anterior 2/5 of tergum III with yellow fascia; pile pale, on terga short, laterally on terga I and II long; tergum I with a more or less horizontal row of 3–4 light yellow setae at lateral margin; sternum III without sclerotized part; sternum IV, 
<figureCitation box="[1156,1266,648,674]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="83.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[200,1373,517,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@83.[189,1399,511,1895]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="Fig. 36. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) ghatsi sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ. A. Sternum IV, ventral view. B. Left surstylus, lateral view. C. Left superior lobe, lateral view. D. Genitalia, right side, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830628/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Fig. 36A</figureCitation>
; sterna VI, VII and VIII simple, with long yellow pile. Genitalia, 
<figureCitation box="[843,928,683,709]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="83.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[200,1373,517,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@83.[189,1399,511,1895]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="Fig. 36. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) ghatsi sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ. A. Sternum IV, ventral view. B. Left surstylus, lateral view. C. Left superior lobe, lateral view. D. Genitalia, right side, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830628/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
B–D: note the symmetrical surstyli and superior lobes.
